        <div class="entry firstpost"><div class="entryh"><div class="entryh-title">
            <a href="#comment" class="entryh-comments">41</a>
            <div class="entry-title-group">
                <h1 class="heading-size-1">6.1 PTR: New Darkmoon Faire Race, Toys, and Changed Heirloom Prices</h1>

                <div class="entryh-byline">
                    posted&nbsp;<span class="date-tip" title="2015/02/08 at 11:01 AM">2015/02/08 at 11:01 AM</span>
                    by <a href="/news&amp;user=perculia" rel="author">perculia</a>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        </div>

    <div class="entryc">
    <div class="background-spacer"></div>        <div id="jfejwiolkso"></div>
<noscript>The Darkmoon Faire is back in town which means we can check out the new additions on the PTR. There's a racing game, sixnew toys, one battle pet (<a href="/npc=90345">Race MiniZep</a>), and four additional vanity items.<br /><ul><li><b>Toys</b>: <a href="/item=122122">Darkmoon Tonk Controller</a>, <a href="/item=122123">Darkmoon Ring-Flinger</a>, <a href="/item=122129">Fire-Eater's Vial</a>, <a href="/item=122126">Attraction Sign</a>, <a href="/item=122120">Gaze of the Darkmoon</a></li><li><b>Vanity Items</b>: <a href="/item=122124">Darkmoon Cannon</a>, <a href="/item=122121">Darkmoon Gazer</a>, <a href="/item=122128">Checkered Flag</a>, <a href="/item=122119">Everlasting Darkmoon Firework</a></li></ul><br /><br />Be sure to check out the <a href="http://www.wowhead.com/guides/world-events/recurring/darkmoon-faire-guide">Darkmoon Faire on live servers</a> as it's a great source of vanity toys and heirlooms, which are getting their <a href="http://www.wowhead.com/news=246129/blizzards-6-1-heirloom-system-preview-friday-update-arcade-blackrock-foundry-tun">own collection system in 6.1</a>.<br /><br /><div class="quote"><b>Note: This is a PTR preview article, and things may change. For up-to-date information on what's on live servers, please read the <a href="http://www.wowhead.com/guides/world-events/recurring/darkmoon-faire-guide">Darkmoon Faire Guide</a>.</b></div><br /><br /><h2 class="heading-size-2">New Darkmoon Faire Game: Racing</h2><br /><br />The racing game from the beta has returned with some modifications! Players race through the Darkmoon Faire woods trying for the fastest possible time for prizes. There are two types of races and four mounts. Players only start off with one race/mount option and more will unlock in later months. This means that you cannot get all the listed achievements and rewards in the first month, but will have to return.<br /><br />There is an introductory quest by the Boardwalk for familiarizing yourself with the race: <a href="/quest=37819">Welcome to the Darkmoon Races</a>. Once that's complete, you're good to complete <b>The Real Race</b>.<br /><br />In this race, you have to hit a blue, green, and red post, and then return to the Starting area. You can speed up your progress several ways.<br /><ul><li>Pick up sprint boosts, which also let you walk on water (useful for reaching the blue post faster).</li><li>Jump on bouncy gears to leap forward--make sure you are angled the right way so you don't go off in the wrong direction.</li><li>Use the special <a href="/spell=179748">Jump To Banner</a> button, on a 10 second cooldown, to leap to the nearest banner and be immune to electrical wires for a few seconds.</li><li>Avoid the electrical wires which stun you.</li></ul><br /><br />There are achievements for completing the race on one of four special racing mounts.<br /><br /><h2 class="heading-size-2">Rewards for the Darkmoon Faire Race</h2><br /><br />There are prizes for completing the Real Big Race within 20 tolls:<br /><ul><li><a href="/achievement=9817">Big Powermonger: Gold</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179251">Powermonger</a>, rewards <a href="/item=122124">Darkmoon Cannon</a>. This shoots you out of a cannon and lets you fly for a minute.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9811">Big Wanderluster: Gold</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179256">Wanderluster</a>, rewards a <a href="/item=122121">Darkmoon Gazer</a>. This item is quite similar to <a href="/spell=126">Eye of Kilrogg</a> and lets you scout out dangerous areas.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9805">Big Rocketeer: Gold</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179252">Rocketeer</a>, rewards a <a href="/item=122125">Race MiniZep Controller</a>. This teaches the battle pet <a href="/npc=90345">Race MiniZep</a>.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9799">Big Race Roadhog</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179750">Racing Strider</a>, rewards a <a href="/item=122128">Checkered Flag</a>. This increases mount speed by 30% for 10 minutes.</li></ul><br /><br />Completing the Real Race within 11 tolls also rewards prizes:<br /><br /><ul><li><a href="/achievement=9785">Powermonger: Gold</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179251">Powermonger</a>, rewards a <a href="/item=122120">Gaze of the Darkmoon</a> toy. This puts a Darkmoon Faire marker over someone's head.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9792">Wanderluster: Gold</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179256">Wanderluster</a>, rewards an <a href="/item=122126">Attraction Sign</a>. This places down a blinking arrow, similar to the ones used as decorations around the Faire.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9764">Rocketeer: Gold</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179252">Rocketeer</a>, rewards an <a href="/item=122119">Everlasting Darkmoon Firework</a>. This is a permanent version of <a href="/item=74142">Darkmoon Firework</a>, a firework with the Faire logo.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9761">Darkmoon Racer Roadhog</a>, for using a <a href="/spell=179750">Racing Strider</a>, rewards a <a href="/item=122129">Fire-Eater's Vial</a>. This sets your breath on fire, like many of the Darkmoon Faire NPCs.</li></ul><br /><br />In addition, these races are good sources of achievement points as there are numerous achievements for completing the races at different speeds.<br /><br /><h2 class="heading-size-2">Darkmoon Faire Heirlooms</h2><br /><br />Heirlooms are still sold at the Darkmoon Faire. They are cheaper as the versions sold go from 1-60 in Patch 6.1, instead of 1-80 as they do now. Your existing heirlooms purchased from the Faire will scale up to 90 automatically when 6.1 hits.<br /><br />Heirlooms are receiving changes in 6.1 as part of the account-wide heirloom collection system--<a href="http://ptr.wowhead.com/news=246129/blizzards-6-1-heirloom-system-preview-friday-update-arcade-blackrock-foundry-tun">read more about it here</a>.<br /><br />Instead of upgrading your heirlooms with the older version + even more prize tickets, you just purchase an item in 6.1 to upgrade your old heirloom.<br /><ul><li><a href="/item=122338">Ancient Heirloom Armor Casing</a> is sold for 100 <a href="/currency=515">Darkmoon Prize Ticket</a> which upgrades an heirloom armor item to 1-90.</li><li><a href="/item=122339">Ancient Heirloom Scabbard</a> is sold for 120 <a href="/currency=515">Darkmoon Prize Ticket</a> which upgrades an heirloom weapon item to 1-90.</li></ul><br /><br />If you just want to collect heirlooms to fill up your collection's tab and get <a href="/item=122703">Chauffeured Chopper</a> quickly, wait until 6.1 to buy them as they are cheaper. If you want to actually use the heirlooms, it is better to buy the lvl 80 version from the Faire right now but skip upgrading it, as it will scale up to 90 in 6.1. This is cheaper than buying a base heirloom and upgrading it to 90 in 6.1.<br /><br /><h2 class="heading-size-2">Rewards for Older Games</h2><br /><br />Several older games are getting achievements and rewards as well.<br /><br /><ul><li><a href="/achievement=9885">Ace Tonk Commander</a> requires you to get 45 hits during the Tonk Challenge. 30 hits are required for <a href="/quest=29434">Tonk Commander</a> so you'll have to keep moving, spamming attacks, and avoiding Zeppelins. This rewards the <a href="/item=122122">Darkmoon Tonk Controller</a> toy.</li><li><a href="/achievement=9894">Triumphant Turtle Tossing</a> requires you to toss 10 rings in one try during the Ring Challenge--a perfect run. The pathing of the turtle has changed in 6.1 and <a href="http://ptr.wowhead.com/item=122123/darkmoon-ring-flinger#comments:id=2100963">this comment</a> explains how you can reliably toss the ring each time. This rewards the <a href="/item=122123">Darkmoon Ring-Flinger</a> toy.</li></ul></noscript>
    </div>
    <div class="entrym" id="endofpost">


