ng the blue post faster).[/li]\n[li]Jump on bouncy gears to leap forward--make sure you are angled the right way so you don't go off in the wrong direction.[/li]\n[li]Use the special [spell=179748] button, on a 10 second cooldown, to leap to the nearest banner and be immune to electrical wires for a few seconds.[/li]\n[li]Avoid the electrical wires which stun you.[/li][/ul]\n\nThere are achievements for completing the race on one of four special racing mounts.\n\n[center][screenshot id=455091 width=250 size=resized][/screenshot] [screenshot id=455092 width=250 size=resized][/screenshot] [screenshot id=455093 width=250 size=resized][/screenshot] [screenshot id=455094 width=250 size=resized][/screenshot] [screenshot id=455095 width=250 size=resized][/screenshot] [screenshot id=455097 width=250 size=resized][/screenshot][/center]\n[h2]Rewards for the Darkmoon Faire Race[/h2]\nThere are prizes for completing the Real Big Race within 20 tolls:\n[screenshot id=454889 width=200 size=resized float=right][/screenshot][ul][li][achievement=9817], for using a [spell=179251], rewards [item=122124]. This shoots you out of a cannon and lets you fly for a minute.[/li]\n\n[li][achievement=9811], for using a [spell=179256], rewards a [item=122121]. This item is quite similar to [spell=126] and lets you scout out dangerous areas.[/li]\n\n[li][achievement=9805], for using a [spell=179252], rewards a [item=122125]. This teaches the battle pet [npc=90345].[/li]\n\n[li][achievement=9799], for using a [spell=179750], rewards a [item=122128]. This increases mount speed by 30% for 10 minutes.[/li][/ul]\n[pad][pad]\nCompleting the Real Race within 11 tolls also rewards prizes:\n\n[screenshot id=265318 width=200 size=resized float=right][/screenshot][ul][li][achievement=9785], for using a [spell=179251], rewards a [item=122120] toy. This puts a Darkmoon Faire marker over someone's head.[/li] \n\n[li][achievement=9792], for using a [spell=179256], rewards an [item=122126]. This places down a blinking arrow, similar to the ones used as decorations around the Faire.[/li]\n\n[li][achievement=9764], for using a [spell=179252], rewards an [item=122119]. This is a permanent version of [item=74142], a firework with the Faire logo.[/li]\n\n[li][achievement=9761], for using a [spell=179750], rewards a [item=122129]. This sets your breath on fire, like many of the Darkmoon Faire NPCs.[/li][/ul]\n\nIn addition, these races are good sources of achievement points as there are numerous achievements for completing the races at different speeds.\n\n[h2]Darkmoon Faire Heirlooms[/h2]\nHeirlooms are still sold at the Darkmoon Faire. They are cheaper as the versions sold go from 1-60 in Patch 6.1, instead of 1-80 as they do now. Your existing heirlooms purchased from the Faire will scale up to 90 automatically when 6.1 hits.\n\nHeirlooms are receiving changes in 6.1 as part of the account-wide heirloom collection system--[url=http://ptr.wowhead.com/news=246129/blizzards-6-1-heirloom-system-preview-friday-update-arcade-blackrock-foundry-tun]read more about it here[/url].\n\n[center][screenshot id=455112 width=450 size=resized][/screenshot] [screenshot id=455113 width=450 size=resized][/screenshot][/center]\n\nInstead of upgrading your heirlooms with the older version + even more prize tickets, you just purchase an item in 6.1 to upgrade your old heirloom.\n[ul][li][item=122338] is sold for 100 [currency=515] which upgrades an heirloom armor item to 1-90.[/li]\n[li][item=122339] is sold for 120 [currency=515] which upgrades an heirloom weapon item to 1-90.[/li][/ul]\n\nIf you just want to collect heirlooms to fill up your collection's tab and get [item=122703] quickly, wait until 6.1 to buy them as they are cheaper. If you want to actually use the heirlooms, it is better to buy the lvl 80 version from the Faire right now but skip upgrading it, as it will scale up to 90 in 6.1. This is cheaper than buying a base heirloom and upgrading it to 90 in 6.1.\n\n[h2]Rewards for Older Games[/h2]\n[screenshot id=455071 width=200 size=resized float=right][/screenshot]Several older games are getting achievements and rewards as well.\n\n[ul][li][achievement=9885] requires you to get 45 hits during the Tonk Challenge. 30 hits are required for [quest=29434] so you'll have to keep moving, spamming attacks, and avoiding Zeppelins. This rewards the [item=122122] toy.[/li]\n\n[li][achievement=9894] requires you to toss 10 rings in one try during the Ring Challenge--a perfect run. The pathing of the turtle has changed in 6.1 and [url=http://ptr.wowhead.com/item=122123/darkmoon-ring-flinger#comments:id=2100963]this comment[/url] explains how you can reliably toss the ring each time. This rewards the [item=122123] toy.[/li][/ul]", "jfejwiolkso", { uid: 3813456, inBlog: 2, allow: Markup.CLASS_ADMIN });

